init_text:
How Do You Think Technology Affects Dating?

Have you had any experience with dating? Have you ever used dating apps? If so, what has it been like for you? If not, why not?

How do you think technology — like apps, Netflix, social media and texting — affects dating and relationships? In your opinion, does it improve or worsen romantic interactions? How so?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When just going to a bar was the best way to meet someone, you were limited to very few people that you'd actually want to talk to after

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Now, the chances of meeting someone on a dating app that really catches your eye has increased exponentially.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Netflix shows us realistic examples of relationships where one or more characters have some kind of disability.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Social media gives us the opportunity to look at the silly sides of being in a relationship as well as sad.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You can research anything on the internet from health to dating to getting married.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A research conducted at the University of Virginia revealed that couples who watch romantic comedy movies tend to have higher marriage satisfaction than those who don't.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The researchers found that while watching romantic comedy movies, loving and caring feelings were enhanced between the partners.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Many believe that the internet has facilitated romantic relationships.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If things don't work out, it becomes easy to end the relationship.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We'd chat a bit here and there, nothing too personal or deep.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We learned about each other, talked about our lives a little and slowly became closer.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He is pretty much my everything right now.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: We were casual for a while, just liking each others' pictures and having fun.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Soon we started text each other more often, and started going out for coffee or for a run.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: It slowly became deeper, we started opening more and getting closer.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Things progressed, we became a couple and have been happy together for just over two and a half years now.
